<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-25T21:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                                <head>No. 465<lb/><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                                <p>According to <persName corresp="#p_HAGERTYJC1">Hagerty</persName>’s diary President <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> and Prime
                                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> had a private conversation for three
                                    quarters of an hour in the President’s office shortly after noon
                                    on June 25. No record of this conversation has been found in
                                    Department of State files. (<persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, <persName corresp="#p_HAGERTYJC1">James C. Hagerty</persName>
                                    papers)</p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>